%% AI worker permission flow (authorizeWorkerAction). See 03-ai-workforce.md
flowchart TB
  Start[worker action request] --> KS{kill switch? global/tenant}
  KS -- yes --> Deny[DENY + audit]
  KS -- no --> WF{AI_WORKFORCE_ENABLED?}
  WF -- no --> Deny
  WF -- yes --> Ten{worker enabled for tenant?}
  Ten -- no --> Deny
  Ten -- yes --> Cap{capability + tool declared?}
  Cap -- no --> Deny
  Cap -- yes --> Perm{invoker holds required permissions?}
  Perm -- no --> Deny
  Perm -- yes --> L5{Level 5 / prohibited action?}
  L5 -- yes --> Deny
  L5 -- no --> L3{autonomy >= L3?}
  L3 -- yes --> Approve[ALLOW - requires approval, no auto-execute + audit]
  L3 -- no --> Allow[ALLOW - may auto-execute (L0-L2/L4) + audit]
